definition: to hand in/to hand over/to seize
to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]

sentences.english: You need to hand in these forms in person.
sentences.chinese: 你必須親自去繳交這些表格。

sentences.english: Please hand in your homework immediately.
Most students paid the fees with Social Welfare Department assistance.
sentences.chinese: 大部分學生以綜援繳交費用。

sentences.english: This is a free online application service with no additional charges to the applicant.
sentences.chinese: 此爲免費網上申購服務，申請者毋須繳交額外費用。

sentences.english: Students should hand in the anamnesis record sheet.
Also submit one copy of your passport or that of your ARC.
sentences.chinese: 請繳交護照或是居留證影本。

sentences.english: Please arrive the Bamboo Room 10 minutes early and pay the tuition fee before the activity.
sentences.chinese: 請於活動前10分鐘於幽竹廳報到，並繳交入場費。

sentences.english: Students who have not yet graduated must submit their diplomas when they report to THU, otherwise, their admission will be canceled.
sentences.chinese: 應屆畢業生須於錄取報到時繳交，否則取銷錄取資格。

sentences.english: Students then write up the results of their experiments, as described in the two writing assignments below.
sentences.chinese: 之後修習生需寫出實驗結果與下面兩個作業，並繳交。
繳交第三篇短論的提案。

sentences.english: All members shall pay in time their membership fee so as to retain their membership.
sentences.chinese: 所有會員必須每年準時繳交指定之會費以確保其會籍。

sentences.english: Payment made before mid- night on the due date will be regarded as on- time payment.
sentences.chinese: 於到期日午夜前繳款會被視作準時繳交。

sentences.english: All members must pay the Foundation Fee when they register as members.
sentences.chinese: 個人會員及團體會員須於入會時繳交基金費。
繳交第一篇短論的提案。

sentences.english: Please specify reasons for applying late payment of tuition fee in next page.
sentences.chinese: 請於下頁空位內填上閣下申請延期繳交學費的原因。

sentences.english: Please submit SGD$10 Administration Fee, and 2 passport size photos.
sentences.chinese: 請繳交新幣十元行政費用與相片兩張。

definition: to pay/to hand over (tax payment etc)
to hand in/to hand over/to seize
to return (sth borrowed etc)/to send back/to refund/to rebate
to report (to the authorities)/to declare (to customs)
